<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Some are visible only to the writer himself;</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">others only to the reader. More & more</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">complex do they become, as the book with the</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">author's name on it goes out to a</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">larger public, to a more complex public, to a</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">public that has emerged sufficiently from</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">the silence of the middle ages to be</l>
<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">educated, partly educated, to desire</l>

<l xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">the private life which is so drab.</l>
